ric` and pre-fills a repeatable seeded test target, such as `echo` on `/mcp/none`, `/mcp/basic`, or `/mcp/oauth`, so the user can rerun the protocol call manually after the broad scenario completes.\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:109:Generic target inputs include short tooltips for new MCP users. Route preset and authorization-helper selections also show an inline explanation of what the current option changes in the outgoing request.\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:125:npm run inspector:ui -- --port 3201\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:130:Run the project-specific inspector when you want the same Mock Server scenario coverage from a command line:\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:133:npm run inspector:mock\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:148:- audit evidence for inspector-created activity\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:151:At the end of a successful run, the local inspector prints a compact diagnostics report. Treat this report as the user-facing proof that the target is speaking standard-facing MCP/OAuth behavior rather than only passing project-internal happy paths.\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:156:npm run inspector:mock -- --base-url http://127.0.0.1:3000\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:162:npm run inspector:mock -- --base-url https://127.0.0.1:3443 --insecure-tls\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:168:ROOT_PASSWORD='change-this' npm run inspector:mock -- --include-reset\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:171:The local inspector creates temporary endpoint, user, client, and token records, then removes the mutable records before exiting. Audit and token history may remain as non-secret evidence, matching the product's audit behavior.\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:178:npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:202:The repository includes `config/mcp-inspector.local.json` for local targets and `config/mcp-inspector.remote.json` for deployed target checks.\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:208:1. Keep the standalone UI scenario runner and CLI inspector aligned so users can choose either visible browser evidence or terminal evidence.\\\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:226:npm run inspe