ream browser Inspector version that shows Completion controls.\\ndocs/FEATURES.md:69:OAuth tokens also carry resource and prompt permission claims. Bearer `resources/list`, `resources/read`, `prompts/list`, `prompts/get`, and `completion/complete` expose only the permitted resource or prompt set.\\ndocs/FEATURES.md:110:- `completion/complete` for prompt arguments and resource-template arguments\\ndocs/FEATURES.md:113:Client-side Sampling, Roots, and Elicitation are not implemented.\\ndocs/FEATURES.md:121:- **Upstream MCP Inspector**: `npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector` for browser and CLI tools/resources/prompts checks. Upstream CLI `0.21.2` does not expose `completion/complete`; use the upstream browser UI or project Generic target for completion.\\ndocs/RELIABILITY.md:35:- `resources/list`, `resources/templates/list`, `resources/read`, `prompts/list`, `prompts/get`, and `completion/complete` must be covered by protocol unit tests before capability advertisement is expanded.\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:29:| /oauth-clients/new, /oauth-clients/[id] | OAuth client workflows | Create, detail, redirects, allowed tools/resources/prompts, secret actions |\\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:8:- MCP clients call `resources/*`, `prompts/*`, and `completion/complete` over existing Streamable HTTP and legacy SSE routes.\\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:15:- Completion supports prompt arguments and resource-template arguments through `completion/complete` with prefix matching, maximum 100 returned values, optional total, and `hasMore`.\\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:16:- No-auth and Basic routes expose all enabled tools/resources/prompts.\\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:17:- OAuth Bearer routes expose only the enabled tools/resources/prompts included in the token permissions.\\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:18:- Unknown, disabled, or unauthorized resources/prompts never leak content. Authentication failures remain `401